00:12:03.230 --> 00:12:06.879
And here's the
3d_x^2-y^2;

00:12:06.879 --> 00:12:08.996
which again,
to see it well,

00:12:08.996 --> 00:12:10.879
you'd have to turn it.
 

00:12:10.879 --> 00:12:14.820
And here's the 4f
orbital.

00:12:14.820 --> 00:12:18.500
So you can see,
especially say in the top ones,

00:12:18.500 --> 00:12:21.566
compared with the atomic
orbital, that it's exactly the

00:12:21.566 --> 00:12:26.158
same general pattern of nodes,
slightly distorted.

00:12:26.158 --> 00:12:29.775
And incidentally,
remember all the n

00:12:29.775 --> 00:12:32.360
equals whatever,
n=3;

00:12:32.360 --> 00:12:35.629
all the orbitals had the same
energy before.

00:12:35.629 --> 00:12:37.759
Now they don't have all the
same energy.

00:12:37.759 --> 00:12:39.710
Notice that they all have
different energies.

00:12:39.710 --> 00:12:41.190
None of them are degenerate.
 

00:12:41.190 --> 00:12:42.460
Why?
 

00:12:42.460 --> 00:12:46.710
Because if you broke the
nucleus apart,

00:12:46.710 --> 00:12:49.509
how stable a thing that has
that general shape,

00:12:49.509 --> 00:12:52.389
like a dumbbell or a cloverleaf
or something,

00:12:52.389 --> 00:12:57.779
how stable the electrons are in
those lumps depends on whether a

00:12:57.779 --> 00:13:00.690
proton got pulled into the lump.
 

00:13:00.690 --> 00:13:03.812
If there happens to be a proton
in the lump, where kinetic

00:13:03.812 --> 00:13:06.003
energy, the node pattern,
wants it to be,

00:13:06.003 --> 00:13:08.028
then that'll be unusually
stable.

00:13:08.028 --> 00:13:12.024
If the protons have been pulled
someplace where there is a node,

00:13:12.024 --> 00:13:15.639
because of kinetic energy,
then it won't be stabilized.

00:13:15.639 --> 00:13:19.975
So that breaks the degeneracy
of these different patterns that

00:13:19.975 --> 00:13:22.250
have the same number of nodes.
 

00:13:22.250 --> 00:13:25.649
It depends on where the -- how
the potential energy changed.

00:13:25.649 --> 00:13:27.918
Okay, now just finally and very
quickly,

00:13:27.918 --> 00:13:30.210
I want to look at
