00:14:22.168 --> 00:14:25.254
It would be a 1s
orbital, and mostly on fluorine,

00:14:25.254 --> 00:14:27.721
because that's where most of
the protons are,

00:14:27.721 --> 00:14:29.629
the most concentrated protons.
 

00:14:29.629 --> 00:14:30.480
So let's look.
 

00:14:30.480 --> 00:14:34.320
There's a smaller scale ball
model,

00:14:34.320 --> 00:14:36.899
so that we can see really small
orbitals,

00:14:36.899 --> 00:14:39.100
and there that's,
