00:26:50.240 --> 00:26:51.529
Prof: You want that?
 

00:26:51.529 --> 00:26:52.559
Student:  Yes.
 

00:26:52.559 --> 00:26:53.650
&gt;
 

00:26:53.650 --> 00:26:57.349
Prof: Okay,
now Claire you're going to help

00:26:57.349 --> 00:26:58.029
me out.
 

00:26:58.029 --> 00:27:00.480
How big is -- that's a number.
 

00:27:00.480 --> 00:27:04.566
It's the product of -- atomic
orbital A assigns numbers

00:27:04.566 --> 00:27:07.818
everywhere in space,
everywhere in space.

00:27:07.818 --> 00:27:11.269
Atomic orbital B assigns
numbers everywhere in space.

00:27:11.269 --> 00:27:14.974
So at some point in space
atomic orbital B assigns a

00:27:14.974 --> 00:27:18.390
number and atomic orbital A
