00:27:32.289 --> 00:27:33.160
Student:  Not very big.
 

00:27:33.160 --> 00:27:36.089
Prof: And how big is
atomic orbital B there?

00:27:36.089 --> 00:27:36.598
Student:  Not very big.
 

00:27:36.598 --> 00:27:39.660
Prof: Now how big is
atomic orbital A here?

00:27:39.660 --> 00:27:40.779
Student:  Very big.
 

00:27:40.779 --> 00:27:42.781
Prof: Okay.
 

00:27:42.781 --> 00:27:49.569
So now, how big an error do we
