00:28:01.919 --> 00:28:03.019
we make an error.
 

00:28:03.019 --> 00:28:04.759
How big is the error?
 

00:28:04.759 --> 00:28:05.750
Student:  Not very big.
 

00:28:05.750 --> 00:28:07.940
Prof: Ah,
it's negligible,

00:28:07.940 --> 00:28:10.200
because it's at great distance.
 

00:28:10.200 --> 00:28:13.519
Okay, so at great distance we
can forget that.

00:28:13.519 --> 00:28:18.619
So now it's easier to take the
square root, right?

00:28:18.619 --> 00:28:19.970
Okay?
 

00:28:19.970 --> 00:28:21.670
The old fox up here, huh?
 

